text: The Coupe de France, also known in English as the French Cup is the premier knockout cup competition in French football organised by the French Football Federation (FFF). ==History== The Coupe de France was formed on 15 January 1917 by the French Interfederal Committee (CFI), an early predecessor of the French Football Federation. ==Champions== Club Winners Runners-up Last final win Last final lost Paris Saint-Germain 16 5 2025 2019 Marseille 10 9 1989 2016 Saint-Étienne 6 4 1977 2020 Lille 6 3 2011 1949 Monaco 5 5 1991 2021 Lyon 5 4 2012 2024 RC Paris 5 3 1949 1990 Red Star 5 1 1942 1946 Bordeaux 4 6 2013 1969 Nantes 4 6 2022 2023 Auxerre 4 2 2005 2015 Rennes 3 4 2019 2014 Strasbourg 3 3 2001 1995 Nice 3 2 1997 2022 Sète 2 4 1934 1942 Sedan 2 3 1961 2005 Sochaux 2 3 2007 1988 Montpellier 2 2 1990 1994 Reims 2 2 1958 2025 Metz 2 1 1988 1938 Guingamp 2 1 2014 1997 CASG Paris 2 – 1925 Olympique de Paris 1 2 1918 1921 Bastia 1 2 1981 2002 CA Paris 1 1 1920 1928 Le Havre 1 1 1959 1920 Club Français 1 – 1931 Cannes 1 – 1932 Roubaix 1 – 1933 Nancy-Lorraine 1 – 1944 Toulouse (1937) 1 – 1957 Nancy 1 – 1978 Lorient 1 – 2002 Toulouse 1 – 2023 Lens – 3 1998 Nîmes – 3 1996 US Quevilly – 2 2012 RC Roubaix – 2 1933 FC Nancy – 2 1962 Angers – 2 2017 FC Lyon – 1 1918 FC Rouen – 1 1925 AS Valentigney – 1 1926 FCO Charleville – 1 1936 SC Fives – 1 1941 ÉF Reims- Champagne – 1 1944 Valenciennes – 1 1951 AS Troyes-Savinienne – 1 1956 Orléans – 1 1980 Calais RUFC – 1 2000 Amiens – 1 2001 LB Châteauroux – 1 2004 Evian – 1 2013 Les Herbiers – 1 2018 ==References== ==External links== * Official page on FFF site Category:Football competitions in Europe
